"a.弯弯曲曲的 【英】 adj.弯弯曲曲的(wind ing) 【考】 labyrinth : tortuous / ornament : decorative(迷宫弯曲/装饰品装 饰)反义词: straightforwatd(笔 直的); direct(直接的) 【记】 tort(弯曲)+uous→弯 曲的 adj. 弯弯曲曲的 = winding; 曲折复杂的 【记】tort转, uous－弯曲的 【类】labyrinth: tortuous = ornament: decorative迷宫弯曲的 = 饰品装饰的 【反】straightforward(adj 正直的; 坦率的); direct(adj 径直的) 【记】源自tort- 扭曲，twist；tortoise 在蜿蜒的小路上爬，比兔子跑一会就休息还快 【相关】torture 折磨，tortuous 曲折的 contort 扭曲，distort 歪曲 extort 敲诈勒索 retort 反驳 tortuous (adj.)  late 14c., ""full of twists and turns,"" from Anglo-French tortuous (12c.), Old French tortuos, from Latin tortuosus ""full of twists, winding,"" from tortus ""a twisting, winding,"" from stem of torquere ""to twist, wring, distort"" (see torque (n.)). Related: Tortuously; tortuousness."
